      <section eId="sec_60_22">
        <num>60.22</num>
        <heading>Rules of evidence; corroboration of accomplice testimony</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_60_22__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The offense charged; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_60_22__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>An offense based upon the same or some of the same facts or\nconduct which constitute the offense charged.\n  3.  A witness who is an accomplice as defined in subdivision two is no\nless such because a prosecution or conviction of himself would be barred\nor precluded by some defense or exemption, such as infancy, immunity or\nprevious prosecution, amounting to a collateral impediment to such a\nprosecution or conviction, not affecting the conclusion that such\nwitness engaged in the conduct constituting the offense with the mental\nstate required for the commission thereof.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
